INSERT INTO tGastExamples VALUES ('CHECK', 'test check', '~#javaj#~6~6   <frames> F, ~3example check~3~6~6   <layout of F>~6~6      EVA, 10, 10, 5, 5~6      ---,  X~6       X , oConsola~6~6#listix#~6~6   <main0>~6      @<chk1>~6      //~6      @<chk2>~6      //~6      @<chk3>~6      //~6      @<chk4>~6      //~6      @<chk5>~6      //~6~6   <chk1>~6      CHECK, VAR, main0, //Not Ok!, VAR, main is False ??~6      //Ok, variable main checked!~6~6   <chk2>~6      CHECK, VAR, main2, //Ok, variable main2 not checked!~6      //Not Ok! CHECK, VAR, main2 is True ??~6~6   <chk3>~6      CHECK, FILE, gastona/gastona.class~6           , ELSE, //Ok, gastona/gastona.class not found as file.~6      //Strange!, gastona/gastona.class is found as file (?)~6~6   <chk4>~6      CHECK, RFILE, gastona/gastona.class~6           , ELSE , //FAIL! gastona/gastona.class should be found as read file!~6      //Ok, gastona/gastona.class checked as read file~6~6   <chk5>~6      CHECK, LINUX, //Operative system seems to be Windows~6      //Operative system seems to be Linux~6~6   <chk6>~6      CHECK, ANDROID, //Running NOT on an Android device~6      //Running on an Android device~6');INSERT INTO tLsxCmdAliases VALUES ('CHECK', 'REQUIRED');INSERT INTO tlsxCmdSyntaxHead VALUES ('CHECK', '1', '3', 'Checks the existence of an Eva variable');
